<poem>
    <meta>
        <title>TO ——</title>
    </meta>
    <stanza>
        <br>I heed not that my earthly lot</br>
        <br>Hath <det value="closed">little</det> of Earth in it,</br>
        <br>That years of love have been <verb value="closed">forgot</verb></br>
        <br>In the <noun value="closed">hatred</noun> of a minute:</br>
    </stanza>
    <stanza>
        <br>I mourn not that the desolate</br>
        <br>Are <adj value="open">happier</adj>, sweet, than I,</br>
        <br>But that you <verb value="closed">sorrow</verb> for my fate</br>
        <br>Who am a <noun value="closed">passer-by</noun>.</br>
    </stanza>
</poem>